Description: Ostracon, fragment from the body of a light-buff coloured pottery jar, interior slightly grooved and exterior covered with a cream-coloured slip, with remains of one line of black-painted hieratic text on the exterior specifying the contents as a commodity of which only part of the name survives.
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (389883) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/389883)
